  "local_port": 36338,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do I keep Instagram private from Facebook friends and contacts?",
  "response": "To keep your Instagram account private from your Facebook friends and contacts, you can follow these steps:\n\n### Make Your Instagram Account Private:\n1. **Open the Instagram App**: Launch the Instagram app on your mobile device.\n2. **Go to Your Profile**: Tap your profile picture in the bottom right corner.\n3. **Access Settings**:\n   - Tap the three horizontal lines (hamburger menu) in the top right corner.\n   - Select **Settings** at the bottom of the menu.\n4. **Privacy**: Tap on **Privacy**.\n5. **Private Account**: Toggle the switch for **Private Account** to the \"On\" position. This will make your account private, meaning only your approved followers can see your posts and stories.\n\n### Manage Linked Accounts:\n1. **Disabling Account Linking**: If your Instagram and Facebook accounts are linked, consider unlinking them:\n   - In the **Settings** menu, tap on **Account**.\n   - Select **Linked Accounts**.\n   - Choose **Facebook** and then select **Unlink Account**.\n\n### Adjust Facebook Privacy Settings:\n1. **Modify Your Facebook Settings**: If you want to prevent your Facebook friends from seeing your Instagram activity:\n   - Open the **Facebook app** and go to the **Settings**.\n   - Navigate to **Privacy** settings.\n   - Manage who can see your activity and posts.\n\n### Limit Searchable Visibility:\n1. **Instagram Search Options**: Ensure your account does not show up in search results:\n   - In the **Privacy** section of Instagram settings, find **Activity Status** and **Connections**. \n   - Turn off any options that allow others to find you through your phone contacts or other methods.\n\n### Block Specific Contacts:\n1. **Block Unwanted Contacts**: If there are specific friends or contacts you want to block:\n   - Go to their profile.\n   - Tap the three dots in the top right corner.\n   - Select **Block**.\n\n### Review Followers:\n1. **Manage Your Followers**: Regularly review and manage your followers to ensure only those you trust have access to your posts.\n\n### Check Sharing Options:\n1. **Stories and Posts**: When sharing content, you can manually select who sees your Stories or posts through the audience selection options for each post or story.\n\nBy following these steps, you can keep your Instagram account more private and limit visibility from your Facebook friends and contacts.",
